    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2010-04-28</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2010-05-13T15:49:40Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Nuclear Power 2021 Act - Amends the Energy Policy Act of 2005 to instruct the Secretary of Energy to implement, through cooperative agreements with private sector partners, a program to: (1) develop a standard design for each of two small modular reactors, at least one of which has a rated capacity of not more than 50 electrical megawatts; (2) obtain a design certification from the Nuclear Regulatory Commission (NRC) for each of the designs by January 1, 2018; and (3) demonstrate the licensing of small modular reactors by developing applications for a combined license for each of the designs so certified, and obtaining a combined license from the NRC for each of the certified designs by January 1, 2021.</p> <p>Requires the Secretary to select proposals for such cooperative agreements through the use of competitive procedures and an impartial review of their scientific and technical merit.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
